Create a project directory; for example

mkdir ~/walk_analyzer

The project directory will contain both the python virtual environment
and the project python files

Create the virtual environment sub-directory

cd ~/walk_analyzer

python3 -m venv walk-venv

Then use pip install to install the modules you need

You must activate the virtual environment.  For example

source ~/walk_analyzer/walk-venv/bin/activate.csh

You will see the user prompt change

Save the configuration by using freeze command

pip freeze > requirements.txt

You can then reinstall modules just be typing

pip install -r requirements.txt

When done you can type

deactivate


